div.p:
That the real ultimatum proposed by the Department of State to the Government of
                    Ecuador to oblige the payment of interests to the railway has caused great
                    surprise;

That the mere demand of the State Department, supported by the threat to prohibit
                    the importation of cocoa, constitutes a hostile act which does not correspond to
                    the recent tokens of sympathy shown towards the United States;

That if the threat is carried out, it would be necessary to explain to the cocoa
                    exporters the real cause, which would be injurious to the American interests in
                    Ecuador;

That the mere publication of the reason would affect the principles of respect
                    for the rights of weaker nations, which rights have been championed, specially
                    of late, by the United States;
